<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 10 at 2:19PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow showers will impact portions of southern
Lewis and Clark County through 300 PM MST...
At 215 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking moderate to heavy snow
showers along a line extending from 14 miles west of Wolf Creek to
Helena. Movement was east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Moderate to heavy snow and visibility as low as a half
mile or less.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hazardous driving conditions.
Locations impacted include...
Helena, Lincoln, East Helena, Wolf Creek, Marysville, York, Craig,
Rimini, Spring Meadow Lake State Park, Canyon Creek, Black Sandy
State Park and Austin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
